{"title_page": "List of Mickey Mouse Mixed-Up Adventures episodes", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date = Mickey Mouse Mixed-Up Adventures}}\n\n{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Mickey and the Roadster Racers'' episodes}}\n''[[Mickey and the Roadster Racers]]'' is an American [[Computer animation|computer]]-[[Animated series|animated]] [[children's television series]] produced by [[Disney Television Animation]]. It is a spin-off of ''[[Mickey Mouse Clubhouse]].'' The series debuted on [[Disney Junior]] and [[Disney Channel]] in the [[United States]] on January 15, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lincoln|first=Ross A.|title=Disney Junior Sets January Launch For ''Mickey And The Roadster Racers''|url=https://deadline.com/2016/12/disney-juniors-mickey-and-the-roadster-racers-to-debut-in-january-1201862550/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=December 2, 2016|date=December 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe series was renewed for a second season on March 15, 2017,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/disney-junior-renews-mickey-and-the-roadster-racers-the-lion-guard-1202043582/|title=Disney Junior Renews ''Mickey and the Roadster Racers'' & ''The Lion Guard''|first1=Liz|last1=Calvario|date=March 15, 2017|website=Deadline Hollywood}}</ref> which premiered on April 13, 2018. A third season began airing on October 14, 2019 under the new title ''Mickey Mouse Mixed-Up Adventures''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/disney-junior-renews-mickey-and-the-roadster-racers-for-season-3-1202338230/|title=Disney Junior Renews ''Mickey And The Roadster Racers'' For Season 3|first=Bruce|last=Haring|date=March 15, 2018|website=Deadline Hollywood}}</ref>\n\n==Series overview==\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n| auxA         = Segments\n\n| color1       = #AE1C1C\n| link1        = <includeonly>List of Mickey Mouse Mixed-Up Adventures episodes</includeonly>#Season 1: Mickey and the Roadster Racers (2017\u201318)\n| auxA1        = 52\n| episodes1    = 26\n| start1       = {{Start date|2017|1|15}}\n| end1         = {{End date|2018|3|23}}\n\n| color2       = #FBE870\n| link2        = <includeonly>List of Mickey Mouse Mixed-Up Adventures episodes</includeonly>#Season 2: Super-Charged (2018\u201319)\n| auxA2        = 50\n| episodes2    = 25\n| start2       = {{Start date|2018|4|13}}\n| end2         = {{End date|2019|8|2}}\n\n| color3       = #87ceeb\n| link3        = <includeonly>List of Mickey Mouse Mixed-Up Adventures episodes</includeonly>#Season 3: Mickey Mouse Mixed-Up Adventures (2019\u201320)\n| auxA3        = 50\n| episodes3    = 25\n| start3       = {{Start date|2019|10|14}}\n| end3         =\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Episodes==\n===Season 1: ''Mickey and the Roadster Racers'' (2017\u201318)===\n*Mickey Mouse, Minnie Mouse, Pluto, Goofy, Daisy Duck, Donald Duck and Cuckoo Loca were present in all episodes in this season.\n{{Episode table |background= #AE1C1C |overall= |season= |title= |director= |writer= |aux2= |aux2T=Storyboards by |airdate= |airdateR=<ref name=\"press\"/> |prodcode= |prodcodeR=<ref name=\"press\">{{cite web|url=http://www.disneyabcpress.com/disneyjunior/shows/mickey-and-the-roadster-racers/episodes|title=Mickey and the Roadster Racers|work=[[Disney Junior|Disney Junior Press]]|accessdate=December 27, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170112200141/http://www.disneyabcpress.com/disneyjunior/shows/mickey-and-the-roadster-racers/episodes/|archive-date=January 12, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=futoncritic>[http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/mickey-and-the-roadster-racers/listings Mickey and the Roadster Racers]. www.[[Futon Critic|futoncritic]].com August 29, 2018</ref>|viewers= |country=US |episodes= \n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1a\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1a\n| Title           = Mickey's Wild Tire!\n| DirectedBy      = Phil Weinstein\n| WrittenBy       = Brian Swenlin\n| Aux2            = Dave Bennett\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|1|15}}\n| ProdCode        = 101a\n| Viewers         = 2.03<ref name=showbuzzdaily1ab2ab>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-sunday-cable-originals-network-finals-1-15-2017.html|title=UPDATED: SHOWBUZZDAILY\u2019s Top 150 Sunday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 1.15.2017|author=Mitch Metcalf|work=Showbuzz Daily|date=January 18, 2017|accessdate=January 20, 2017}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Mickey surprises Jiminy Johnson ([[Jimmie Johnson]]), a racing champion, with the tire from his first roadster. Displeased that his own gift for Jiminy won't impress him, Pete plans to be the one to give Jiminy the tire.\n| LineColor       = AE1C1C\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1b\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1b\n| Title           = Sittin' Kitty\n| DirectedBy      = Broni Likomanov\n| WrittenBy       = Thomas Hart<br>{{StoryTeleplay|ex1label=Story editor|ex1=Thomas Hart}}\n| Aux2            = Dave Williams\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|1|15}}\n| ProdCode        = 101b\n| Viewers         = 2.03<ref name=showbuzzdaily1ab2ab/>\n| ShortSummary    = Minnie and Daisy are petsitting Hilda's pet Snowpuff. When they find a cat there, they think it's Snowpuff and pursue it when it escapes from the house.\n| LineColor       = AE1C1C\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2a\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2a\n| Title           = Goofy Gas!\n| DirectedBy      = Broni Likomanov\n| WrittenBy       = Mark Seidenberg\n| Aux2            = Dave Williams\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|1|15}}\n| ProdCode        = 102a\n| Viewers         = 1.98<ref name=showbuzzdaily1ab2ab/>\n| ShortSummary    = Goofy invents the fuel that makes the roadsters go faster. Though it has various side effects on the roadsters during a race when Chip and Dale run out of the usual fuel.\n| LineColor       = AE1C1C\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2b\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2b\n| Title           = Little Big Ape\n| DirectedBy      = Broni Likomanov\n| WrittenBy       = Jennifer Muro<br>{