/year-end/2006/alternative-songs |title=Alternative Songs \u2013 Year-End 2006 |work=Billboard |accessdate=September 6, 2018}}</ref>\n| 16\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.nin.com/ Nine Inch Nails official website]\n\n{{Nine Inch Nails}}\n\n[[Category:Nine Inch Nails songs]]\n[[Category:2006 singles]]\n[[Category:Canadian Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Alternative Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Music based on Nineteen Eighty-Four]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by Francis Lawrence]]\n[[Category:Nothing Records singles]]\n[[Category:Interscope Records singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Trent Reznor]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Trent Reznor]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Alan Moulder]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Nine Inch Nails song}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Every Day Is Exactly the Same\n| cover      = Edietscover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Nine Inch Nails]]\n| album      = [[With Teeth]]\n| released   = April 4, 2006\n| format     = [[CD single]]\n| recorded   = 2004\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = \n| length     = 4:56\n| label      = [[Interscope Records|Interscope]]/[[Nothing Records|Nothing]]\n| writer     = [[Trent Reznor]]\n| producer   = [[Trent Reznor]], [[Alan Moulder]]\n| prev_title = [[Only (Nine Inch Nails song)|Only]]\n| prev_year  = 2005\n| next_title = [[Survivalism (song)|Survivalism]]\n| next_year  = 2007\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Nine Inch Nails discography#Chronology|Halo numbers]]\n | type       = studio\n | prev_title = [[Only (Nine Inch Nails song)|Halo 20]]\n | prev_year  = 2005\n | title      = Halo 21\n | year       = 2006\n | next_title = [[Beside You in Time|Halo 22]]\n | next_year  = 2007\n}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Every Day Is Exactly the Same'''\" is the third [[single (music)|single]] by American [[industrial rock]] band [[Nine Inch Nails]] from their album ''[[With Teeth]]''. It is the twenty-first official [[Nine Inch Nails]] release. The commercial single was released on April 4, 2006 as an [[Extended play|EP]]. It was also billed as the companion [[remix]] disc to ''[[With Teeth]]''{{cn|date=April 2019}}, much to the chagrin of Trent Reznor{{cn|date=April 2019}}.\n\nThe radio single reached #1 on the Billboard Modern Rock singles chart in the [[Modern Rock Tracks]] category and #12 in the [[Mainstream Rock Tracks]] category. The song also reached number one on the [[Canadian Singles Chart]], and received a nomination for ''Best Hard Rock Performance'' at the 49th annual Grammy Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grammy.com/GRAMMY_Awards/49th_Show/list.aspx |archive-url=http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20090710131212/http://www.grammy.com/GRAMMY_Awards/49th_Show/list.aspx |archive-date=July 10, 2009|title=49th Annual Grammy Awards Nominee List|publisher=The Recording Academy|date=December 7, 2006|accessdate=December 7, 2006|url-status=dead}}</ref> Though a planned music video was scrapped in the post-production stage,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theninhotline.net/news/archives/backissue.php?y=06&m=4#1144942551|title=EDIETS Video to Air TODAY on MTV!|publisher=The NIN Hotline|date=April 13, 2006|accessdate=January 10, 2008}}</ref> \"Every Day Is Exactly the Same\" still topped [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'s 2006 year-end [[Hot Dance Singles Sales]] chart, it has so far spent 94 weeks on the chart.<ref>\n\n{{cite magazine|url=http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/yearend/2006/charts/dsl_singl.jsp|title=Billboard 2006 Year in Music|magazine=Billboard|date=December 17, 2006|accessdate=December 17, 2006|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070106114530/http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/yearend/2006/charts/dsl_singl.jsp|archivedate=January 6, 2007|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Video==\n[[File:EDIETS musicvideo.jpg|thumb|250px|left|The only officially released image from the production of the scrapped \"Every Day is Exactly the Same\" music video.]]\nAccording to [https://web.archive.org/web/20060902131840/http://www.nin.com/thespiral/ The Spiral], the [[music video]] for \"Every Day Is Exactly the Same\", directed by [[Francis Lawrence]], was canceled in post-production. An image of a [[clapperboard]] and in the background what appeared to be [[water tank]] with a 3-lead [[ECG]] appeared on the official Nine Inch Nails website, but was later taken down.\n\nThere is also a studio cut video for the song. It can be seen on ''[[Beside You In Time]]''.\n\n==Release and reception==\n[[Allmusic]] gave a generally favorable review of the EP, describing its various remixes as \"actually better than the original versions\".  Allmusic described the \"Sam Fog vs. Carlos D Mix\" of \"Every Day Is Exactly the Same\" as \"sleekly ominous\", and concluded that the track rendered \"NIN's increasingly claustrophobic, insular music sound fresh again\".<ref>{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r828851|pure_url=yes}}\n  | website = [[Allmusic]]\n  | title = Every Day Is Exactly the Same EP > Overview\n  | accessdate = July 10, 2008\n  | first = Stephen Thomas\n  | last = Erlewine}}</ref>  [[Pitchfork Media]] was not as positive towards the last mix, however, labeling it as the most disappointing track on the release and calling it \"cold and ordinary\".<ref name=\"Pitchfork review\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pitchforkmedia.com/article/record_review/20397/Nine_Inch_Nails_Every_Day_Is_Exactly_the_Same_EP |title=Every Day is Exactly the Same EP |publisher=[[Pitchfork Media]] |first=David |last=Raposa |date=April 10, 2006 |accessdate=July 10, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080422034706/http://www.pitchforkmedia.com/article/record_review/20397/Nine_Inch_Nails_Every_Day_Is_Exactly_the_Same_EP |archivedate=April 22, 2008 }}</ref>  Pitchfork was more positive towards the other tracks however, labeling the El-P mix as \"a harrowing (and somewhat cloying) experience\" and concluding of the DFA mix that \"the treatment works beautifully.\"<ref name=\"Pitchfork review\" />\n\n==Use in popular culture==\nThe song is featured in the 2008 film ''[[Wanted (2008 film)|Wanted]]'', where it became the film's most recognizable song.\n\nThis song is played in the CBS show ''[[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series)|Hawaii Five-0]]'', in the beginning of the 15th episode of the third season, entitled \"Hookman\".\n\nThis song is played in the show ''[[Criminal Minds]]'' (first season, second episode, 1 minute 27 seconds in). The episode is titled \"Compulsion\".\n\n==Formats and track listings==\nAll songs by [[Trent Reznor]].\n\n===U.S. CD EP===\n<!-- Interscope(?) catalog # here -->\n# \"Every Day Is Exactly the Same\" \u2013 4:57\n# \"[[The Hand That Feeds]]\" ([[DFA Records|DFA]] Mix) \u2013 9:03\n# \"The Hand That Feeds\" ([[Photek]] Straight Mix) \u2013 7:47\n# \"[[Only (Nine Inch Nails song)|Only]]\" ([[El-Producto|El-P]] Mix) \u2013 4:22\n# \"Only\" ([[Richard X]] Mix) \u2013 7:25\n# \"Every Day Is Exactly the Same\" ([[Sam Fogarino|Sam Fog]] vs. [[Carlos Dengler|Carlos D]] Mix) \u2013 5:03\n\n===Japan CD EP===\n<!-- Record label name & catalog # here -->\n# \"Every Day Is Exactly the Same\" \u2013 4:57\n# \"[[The Hand That Feeds]]\" ([[DFA Records|DFA]] Mix) \u2013 9:03\n# \"The Hand That Feeds\" ([[Photek]] Straight Mix) \u2013 7:47\n# \"[[Only (Nine Inch Nails song)|Only]]\" ([[El-Producto|El-P]] Mix) \u2013 4:22\n# \"Only\" ([[Richard X]] Mix) \u2013 7:25\n# \"Every Day Is Exactly the Same\" ([[Sam Fogarino|Sam Fog]] vs. [[Carlos Dengler|Carlos D]] Mix) \u2013 5:03\n# \"The Hand That Feeds\" (Photek Dub Mix) \u2013 7:52\n# \"Love Is Not Enough\" (Live at Rehearsals) \u2013 3:51\n\n===Promo 12\"===\n(Remixes By Sam Fog And Carlos D. From [[Interpol (band)|Interpol]])\n<!-- Interscope(?) catalog # here -->\n# Everyday Is Exactly The Same \u2013 Main Mix \u2013 5:03\n# Everyday Is Exactly The Same \u2013 Edit \u2013 4:09\n# Everyday Is Exactly The Same \u2013 Full Vocals \u2013 4:12\n\n===<!-- what country? -->Promo CD===\n<!-- Interscope(?) catalog # here -->\n# Everyday Is Exactly The Same \u2013 Edit \u2013 3:51\n# Everyday Is Exactly The Same \u2013 [[Interpol (band)|Interpol]] Mix Edit \u2013 4:09\n# Everyday Is Exactly The Same \u2013 LP Version \u2013 4:56\n\n==Personnel==\n*[[Trent Reznor]] \u2013 vocals and various instruments\n*[[Dave Grohl]] \u2013 drums\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Chart\n! Peak<br />position\n|-\n|Canada ([[Canadian Singles Chart|Nielsen SoundScan]])\n|align=\"center\"| 1\n|-\n|Canada Rock Top 30 ([[Radio & Records]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-RandR/2000s/2006/RR-2006-04-07.pdf|title=RR Canada Rock Top 30|p=62|accessdate=November 19, 2019}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"| 4\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Billboard Hot 100|Hot 100]]<ref name=\"Billboard charts search\">{{cite magazine|title=Billboard Music Charts \u2013 Search Results \u2013 Nine Inch Nails|magazine=Billboard|url=http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/esearch/searchResult.jsp?No=0&Ntt=nine+inch+nails&Ntk=Keyword&Ntx=mode+matchallpartial&an=bbcom&Ex=1&N=37&Ns=FORMATTED_DATE%7c0|accessdate=September 28, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071011144359/http://billboard.com/bbcom/esearch/searchResult.jsp?No=0&Ntt=nine+inch+nails&Ntk=Keyword&Ntx=mode+matchallpartial&an=bbcom&Ex=1&N=37&Ns=FORMATTED_DATE|archivedate=October 11, 2007|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"| 56\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Modern Rock Tracks]]<ref name=\"Billboard charts search\" />\n|align=\"center\"| 1\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Mainstream Rock Tracks]]<ref name=\"Billboard charts search\" />\n|align=\"center\"| 12\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Pop 100]]<ref name=\"Billboard charts search\" />\n|align=\"center\"| 48\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Hot Dance Singles Sales]]<ref>[{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=nine inch nails|chart=Dance/Electronic Single